row\"{{singlechart|New Zealand|36|artist=Demi Lovato feat. Cher Lloyd|song=Really Don't Care|accessdate=September 20, 2015}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|Scotland ([[Official Charts Company]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/scottish-singles-chart/20140713/41/|title=13 July 2014 - 19 July 2014|publisher=The Official UK Charts Company|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|50\n|-\n{{singlechart|Slovakdigital|22|year=2014|week=34|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 30, 2014}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKchartstats|92|artist=Demi Lovato|rowheader=true|accessdate=July 16, 2014}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|26|artist=Demi Lovato|accessdate=July 1, 2014}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Billboardadultpopsongs|25|artist=Demi Lovato|accessdate=July 1, 2014}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Billboarddanceairplay|18|artist=Demi Lovato|accessdate=September 13, 2014}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Billboarddanceclubplay|1|artist=Demi Lovato|accessdate=July 1, 2014}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Billboardpopsongs|7|artist=Demi Lovato|accessdate=July 1, 2014}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2014)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada (Canadian Hot 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2014/canadian-hot-100|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 11, 2014|title=2014 Year End Charts&nbsp;\u2013 Top Canadian Hot 100}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 99\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Mainstream Top 40 (''Billboard'')<ref name=\"billboard.com\">{{cite web|title=Demi Lovato Album & Song Chart History|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300744/demi-lovato/chart|publisher=[[Billboard charts|Billboard]] [[Twitter Top Tracks]] for Demi Lovato|accessdate=April 18, 2015}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|44\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Hot Dance Club Songs (''Billboard'')<ref name=\"billboard.com\"/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|title=Really Don%27t Care|artist=Demi Lovato|type=single|region=United States|award=Platinum{{sup|{{Dagger}}}}\n|salesamount=952,000|salesref=<ref name=\"ussales\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true|nosales=yes|noshipments=yes}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of number-one dance singles of 2014 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{YouTube|id=OJGUbwVMBeA|title=\"Really Don't Care\" music video}}\n{{Demi Lovato}}\n{{Cher Lloyd}}\n\n[[Category:2013 songs]]\n[[Category:2014 singles]]\n[[Category:Cher Lloyd songs]]\n[[Category:Demi Lovato songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Carl Falk]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Demi Lovato]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Rami Yacoub]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Savan Kotecha]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Rami Yacoub]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related songs]]\n[[Category:Torch songs]]\n[[Category:Songs about betrayal]]\n[[Category:Hollywood Records singles]]\n[[Category:Songs about bullying]]\n[[Category:Songs with feminist themes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Really Don't Care\n| cover      = Demi Lovato Really Don't Care (Official Single Cover).png\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Demi Lovato]] featuring [[Cher Lloyd]]\n| album      = [[Demi (album)|Demi]]\n| B-side     = [[Nightingale (Demi Lovato song)|Nightingale]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2014|5|20}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Dance-pop]]\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=21}}\n| label      = [[Hollywood Records|Hollywood]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Demi Lovato]]|[[Carl Falk]]|[[Savan Kotecha]]|[[Rami Yacoub]]|[[Cher Lloyd]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Carl Falk|Rami Yacoub}}\n| chronology = [[Demi Lovato]]\n| prev_title = [[Somebody to You]]\n| prev_year  = 2014\n| next_title = [[Up (Olly Murs song)|Up]]\n| next_year  = 2014\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Cher Lloyd]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Sirens (Cher Lloyd song)|Sirens]]\n | prev_year  = 2014\n | title      = Really Don't Care\n | year       = 2014\n | next_title = [[Activated]]\n | next_year  = 2016\n}}\n}}\n\"'''Really Don't Care'''\" is a song by American singer [[Demi Lovato]], featuring English singer [[Cher Lloyd]]. The song was released on May 20, 2014,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases |title=Top 40/Mainstream > Future Releases |publisher=All Access Music Group |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6PhFKbyFS |archivedate=May 19, 2014 |accessdate=June 27, 2014}}</ref> as the fourth and final single from her fourth studio album ''[[Demi (album)|Demi]]'' (2013). The two co-wrote the song along with [[Savan Kotecha]] and its producers [[Carl Falk]] and [[Rami Yacoub]]. The song has been certified platinum by [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]]. \"Really Don't Care\" is Lovato's third number one on the US Dance chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-09-06/dance-club-play-songs|title=Hot Dance Club Songs |work=Billboard|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc |date= September 6, 2014|accessdate=August 28, 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Composition ==\n\"Really Don't Care\" is an uptempo [[dance-pop]] song, with influences of [[bubblegum pop]],<ref name=\"billboard demi review\">{{cite web|last=Lipshutz|first=Jason|title=Demi Lovato, 'Demi': Track-By-Track Review|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1561233/demi-lovato-demi-track-by-track-review|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=October 12, 2013}}</ref> that runs for three minutes and twenty-one seconds. Lloyd makes a brief appearance during the bridge. Lyrically, the song is a message of defiance to a former lover, with Lovato confidently singing such lines as, \"Even if the stars and moon collide, I never want you back into my life.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Erin|first=Adrienne|title=Pop Topper of the Week: Demi Lovato \u2013 'Really Don't Care' (feat. Cher Lloyd)|url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/Adrienne_Erin/2013/05/14/pop_topper_of_the_week_demi_lovato_re|publisher=StarPulse.com|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref> The song is set in the key of [[G major]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Demi Lovato \"Really Don't Care\" Sheet Music|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0117972&|publisher=Music Notes|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref>\nLovato originally wrote the song as a breakup song. She wanted to make it a more empowering song. Lovato said in an interview, \"I wanted to make it more empowering. When I thought of the lyrics 'really don\u2019t care', it made me think of bullying, and made me think of the LGBT community, who deal with that so often, but they accept themselves.\"<ref name=LGBT>{{cite web|url=http://www.refinery29.com/2014/06/70450/demi-lovato-pride-parade|title=Demi Lovato Really, Truly Has Pride|author=Norris, John|date=2014-06-30|accessdate=2014-06-30}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\n''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' writer Jason Lipshutz praised Lovato's \"sassy\" confidence on the track, which effectively showcases her \"overpowering pipes\". He also commented positively on the placement of the song on the track list, noting that \"Really Don't Care\" serves a \"buoyant reprieve\" after more emotionally heavy tracks.<ref name=\"billboard demi review\"/> Sam Lansky of ''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'' described the song as \"irresistibly spunky\", but found Lloyd's short feature to be superfluous.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lansky|first=Sam|title=Demi Lovato\u2019s \u2018Demi\u2019: Album Review|url=http://www.idolator.com/7457954/demi-lovato-demi-album-review/|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|publisher=[[Spin Media]]|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref> [[4Music]] called the song \"a brilliant break-up survival anthem that sticks it to every annoying ex ever\".<ref name=\"4music\">{{cite episode |title=This Week's Fresh Music Top 20|series=Fresh Music Top 20|network=[[4Music]]|airdate=10 August 2014}}</ref> On the other hand, Melinda Newman of ''[[HitFix]]'' found the song to be too generic, comparing it to [[Icona Pop]]'s breakout hit \"[[I Love It (Icona Pop song)|I Love It]]\" (2012).<ref>{{cite news|last=Newman|first=Melinda|title=Demi Lovato's new album 'Demi': Review|url=http://www.hitfix.com/news/demi-lovatos-new-album-demi-review|work=[[HitFix]]|accessdate=October 13, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Commercial performance==\nBefore it was released as a single, \"Really Don't Care\" debuted on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number 98. After it was released as a single, it peaked at number 26 making it Lovato's eighth top 40 entry on the Hot 100 and making Cher Lloyd's third entry on that chart and second top 40 single since her song \"[[Want U Back]]\". On the US Dance Chart, it became Lovato's third number one and Lloyd's first number one on that chart. As of October 2017, \"Really Don't Care\" has sold over 952,000 digital downloads in the United States.<ref name=\"ussales\">{{cite news|title=Ask Billboard: Demi Lovato's Career Album & Song Sales|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7998706/demi-lovato-21-savage-tom-petty-ask-billboard|work=Billboard|date=October 15, 2017|accessdate=October 15, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Music videos ==\n=== Background and synopsis ===\nThe official music video was released on June 26, 2014, although few teasers for the video were previously uploaded on Lovato's official [[YouTube]] channel.<ref>{{cite web |last=Malkin |first=Marc |title=Demi Lovato's New Teaser for Her 'Really Don't Care' Video\u2014See It Now! |url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/554165/demi-lovato-s-new-teaser-for-her-really-don-t-care-video-see-it-now |work=E! Online |accessdate=June 25, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"eonline-554728\">{{cite web |date=June 26, 2014 |last=Johnson |first=Zach |title=Demi Lovato's 'Really Don't Care' Music Video Features a Surprise Cameo From Wilmer Valderrama! |url=http://de.eonline.com/news/554728/demi-lovato-s-really-don-t-care-music-video-features-a-surprise-cameo-from-wilmer-valderrama |work=E! Online |accessdate=June 26, 2014}}</ref> The video starts off with Lovato expressing her support for the LGBT community and saying that ''\"[her] Jesus loves all.\"'' After that, the music starts and Lovato is seen singing her single at the parade. The video was filmed on June 8, 2014 at the [[Pride parade|LA Pride Parade]] and features cameo appearances from [[Perez Hilton]], [[Kat Graham]], [[Shane Bitney Crone]], [[BriaAndChrissy|Bria Kam and Chrissy Chambers]],<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/user/BriaAndChrissy/ Bria and Chrissy's YouTube channel] YouTube.com</ref> [[John Lloyd Taylor|John Taylor]], [[Travis Barker]] and [[Wilmer Valderrama]].<ref name=\"eonline-554728\"/><ref>{{cite web |last=Ableson |first=Jon |title=Demi Lovato Releases 'Really Don't Care' (ft. Cher Lloyd) Music Video |url=http://www.alterthepress.com/2014/06/demi-lovato-releases-really-dont-care.html |work=Alter The Press! |accessdate=June 26, 2014}}</ref> Cher Lloyd also appears during the bridge part of the song. It was directed by [[Ryan Pallotta]], who collaborated with Lovato from her previous music videos, \"[[Neon Lights (Demi Lovato song)|Neon Lights]]\" and \"[[Made in the USA (Demi Lovato song)|Made in the USA]]\".\n\n=== Lyric video ===\nThe lyric video was uploaded on May 14, 2014 on Lovato's [[Vevo]] account. The video features the lyrics of the song above several shots of Brazilian fans [[lip sync]]ing the song as well as some scenes from concerts where Lovato performs the song during the [[Neon Lights Tour|concert tour]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ryanseacrest.com/2014/05/14/demi-lovato-fans-star-in-really-dont-care-lyric-video/|title=Demi Lovato Fans Star in \u2018Really Don\u2019t Care\u2019 Lyric Video|publisher=Ryan Seacrest|last=Perricone|first=Kathleen|accessdate=May 14, 2014}}</ref> During the video, Lovato makes an appearance to surprise some of the fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1824601/watch-demi-lovato-prank-these-lovatics-in-her-really-dont-care-lyric-video/|title=Watch Demi Lovato Prank These Lovatics In Her \u2018Really Don\u2019t Care\u2019 Lyric Video|publisher=[[MTV]]|accessdate=May 14, 2014|last=Garibaldi|first=Christina}}</ref> At the end, a message is displayed to thank the Brazilian fans for helping out with the filming of the lyric video.\n\n==Live performances==\nLovato performed the song on several occasions before its official release as a single. Once released in May 2014, performances include on the Season 13 Live Final of American Idol,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americanidol.com/videos/season_xiii_performances/idol-finale-demi-lovato-top-13-girls-really-dont-care-and-neon-lights|title=Idol Finale - Demi Lovato & Top 13 Girls \"Really Don't Care\" and \"Neon Lights\"|accessdate=February 4, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819091051/http://www.americanidol.com/videos/season_xiii_performances/idol-finale-demi-lovato-top-13-girls-really-dont-care-and-neon-lights |archivedate=August 19, 2014 }}</ref> ''[[Good Morning America]]'' Summer Concert Series, ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'', and the [[2014 Teen Choice Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Torrelio|first1=Sebastian|title=Best and Worst of the 2014 Teen Choice Awards|url=https://variety.com/2014/scene/vpage/teen-choice-awards-best-and-worst-2014-1201280075/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=August 16, 2014|date=August 11, 2014}}</ref> The song was also included in the setlists for [[The Neon Lights Tour]] and the [[Demi World Tour]]. Furthermore, the song was part of Lovato's setlist at the 2015 [[iHeartRadio Music Festival]] on September 18\u201319, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=iHeartRadio Music Festival 2015 Day 1: 41 Things You Have to See|last=Atkinson|first=Katie|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/music-festivals/6700626/iheartradio-music-festival-what-you-missed|accessdate=October 18, 2015|date=September 19, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Year\n!scope=\"col\"|Award\n!scope=\"col\"|Category\n!scope=\"col\"|Work\n!scope=\"col\"|Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2014\n| [[Young Hollywood Awards]]\n| \"Song of the Summer/DJ Replay\"\n|rowspan=\"7\"|\"Really Don't Care\"\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|\"Best Lyric Video\"\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music \u2013 Summer Song|Choice Summer Song]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Teen Choice Award for Choice Music - Break-Up Song|Choice Break-Up Song]]\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Radio Disney Music Awards]]\n| Best Breakup Song\n|{{Nominated}}\n|-\n| Best Collaboration\n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n==Formats and track listings==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n*'''Digital download (Remixes EP)'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/really-dont-care-remixes-ep/id908195817|title=Really Don't Care Remixes - EP by Demi Lovato on Apple Music|website=itunes.apple.com|accessdate=December 6, 2017}}</ref>\n#\"Really Don't Care\" (feat. Cher Lloyd) - 3:20\n#\"Really Don't Care\" (DJLW Remix) - 4:30\n#\"Really Don't Care\" (Toy Armada & DJ GRIND Remix)- 5:35\n#\"Really Don't Care\" ([[Cole Plante]] Remix) - 5:07\n#\"Really Don't Care\" ([[Digital Dog]] Club Remix) - 5:07\n\n*'''Digital download (Remixes)'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/really-dont-care-remixes-single/id894755822|title=Really Don't Care Remixes